ｐゴシック\",sans-serif;\"=\"ｐゴシック',sans-serif;'\" style=\"margin:0mm;font-size:medium;font-family:;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;\">Topic:&nbsp;Handing in term-end paper and instructions for rewriting if necessary</span></p>", "<span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;background-image:none;background-position:0% 0%;background-size:auto;background-repeat:repeat;background-attachment:scroll;background-origin:padding-box;background-clip:border-box;\">Reworking and rewriting final paper if necessary&nbsp;</span>"]}, "評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["Texts will be distributed in class"], "参考文献・資料/Reference books0": ["Information regarding reference books will be given in class"], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students0": ["Standard evaluation"], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students1": ["Each course is positioned within the curriculum in accordance with the diploma policy andcurriculum policy established by each undergraduate/graduate school. By proceeding with the study of this course with an awareness of the DP and CP, the following abilities expected by each undergraduate/graduate school will be developed.General Foundation Courses (Practical Orientation):1. Problem-solving skills: the ability to proactively identify problems and solve them based on appropriate methods.2. Understanding and analytical skills regarding international issues: the ability to understand and analyze various regions of the world from different perspectives in the humanities and social sciences.3. Ethical Values: Acquiring it though ‘liberal arts education for human growth’ based on Christian principles."], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students2": ["Direct feedback in class and via E-mail"], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["その他／Others (99)", "100 %", "See below"], "成績評価Grading2": ["備考　Note Students will be graded based on 60% of the standard evaluation (assignments 10%; presentation 20%; contribution to class 30%) and&nbsp;40% of the regular report (approximately 2500 words). The report will be regarded as a \"mini-thesis\" and should be formatted and written in a strict manner similar to a graduation thesis.NOTE: As a general rule, the credits will not be granted to students, who miss more than one-third of the class sessions. Handing in final thesis is a compulsory requirement for receiving the credits."], "更新日時/Date of Update0": ["2026年02月19日 18時07分13秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "水曜１時限／Wednesday 1", "秋学期／Fall", "Ｇ－ＩＳ院共同研究室"]}, "campas": 0, "name": "【100】Basic Seminar B　２／Basic Seminar B [EN]", "管理部署": 10, "単位数": 2, "担当者": "ブングシェ　Ｈ．Ｒ．（BUNGSCHE HOLGER ROBERT） ", "履修基準年度": "１年", "履修登録方法": "予備登録", "開講期": 2, "時限1": 14, "時限1_term": 1, "評価1": 6, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\nStudents will be graded based on 60% of the standard evaluation (assignments 10%; presentation 20%; contribution to class 30%) and 40% of the regular report (approximately 2500 words). The report will be regarded as a \"mini-thesis\" and should be formatted and written in a strict manner similar to a graduation thesis.\nNOTE: As a general rule, the credits will not be granted to students, who miss more than one-third of the class sessions. Handing in final thesis is a compulsory requirement for receiving the credits."}